B.Ph=new A.T(B.ad,"CAT III Completion Examples",null,B.Tv,null,null)
B.Qa=new A.T(B.ae,"\u2708\ufe0f Exam Tip",'CAT II/III key distinctions for exams:\n\u2022 **DH** = Decision Height (radio altimeter based, CAT II/III)\n\u2022 **DA** = Decision Altitude (barometric, CAT I)\n\u2022 **RVR** = Runway Visual Range (measured by transmissometers)\n\u2022 A CAT IIIB approach may be conducted with **no Decision Height** if auto-rollout/auto-brake available\n\u2022 LVP does NOT cancel low-visibility departures automatically \u2014 there are separate LVT minima\n\u2022 "Required visual reference" for CAT III is **less** than for CAT I (may be just runway edge lights)',null,null,null)
